  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(24) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Thrust them into the inner prison.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Those who have seen anything of the prisons of the Roman empire, as, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "e.g., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the Mamertine dungeon at Rome itself, can picture to themselves the darkness and foulness of the den into which Paul and his friend were now thrust: the dark cavern-like cell, below the ground, the damp and reeking walls, the companionship of the vilest outcasts. And, as if this were not enough, they were fastened in the “stocks.” St. Luke uses the Greek term ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "xylon, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the same as is used sometimes for the cross (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 5:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The technical Latin word was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "nervus.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Like the English stocks, it was a wooden frame with five holes, into which head and feet and arms were thrust, and the prisoner left in an attitude of “little-ease.” Here, however, it would seem, the feet only were fastened, the rest of the body being left lying on the ground. If the Received version of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 13:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 33:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which follows the LXX. and the Vulgate, be correct, the punishment was common at a very early period in the East. (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 29:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
