  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Who having received such a charge,.... So strict an one from the magistrates, was doubly careful and diligent: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "thrust them into the inner prison: the innermost part of it, the lowest or furthest part of the prison; so that there were the more doors, bolts, and bars, to break open, and pass through, should they attempt to make their escape: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and made their feet fast in the stocks; or \"wood\", a wooden machine, in which the feet of prisoners were put for security, and which we call \"the stocks\"; some say it was such an one, in which the neck as well as the feet were put, and so might be the same with our \"pillory\". ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and made their feet fast in the stocks; or \"wood\", a wooden machine, in which the feet of prisoners were put for security, and which we call \"the stocks\"; some say it was such an one, in which the neck as well as the feet were put, and so might be the same with our \"pillory\". ",
            "children": []
